name: CommonChildhoodBacterialInfections
title: Common Childhood Bacterial Infections
purpose: (Clinical Focus: The intent of this grouping value set is to capture common childhood infections for which antibiotic prescription may be indicated, and which tend to occur in conjunction with otitis media),(Data Element Scope: Diagnosis codes for conditions occurring most commonly in otherwise healthy children that are frequently reasons for antibiotic prescription),(Inclusion Criteria: Diagnosis codes appearing most frequently concurrently with otitis media in an unselected population of children 12 years old or younger for infections in which bacterial pathogens are a common consideration.  The diagnosis code for "Acute pharyngitis" is included, despite presence of a more specific code for streptococcal pharyngitis, based on assessment of code utilization in a large pediatric health system.),(Exclusion Criteria: Diagnosis codes reflecting likely viral origin)
